          So I've noticed for a long time websites like Whoscored love to inflate, and outright lie, about the stats of one player in particular: Messi. Watch this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KPCvHfyvb-g Now count the amount of times Messi is dispossessed. Never mind, I'll do it for you. It happens a total of 10 times. More specifically @ 00:48, 00:52, 1:51, 2:05, 2:49, 3:07, 3:35, 5:20, 5:50, and 5:57 Now go to Whoscored.com and look up Messi's "dispossessed" stat for that game. You know what's there? Twice. According to them, he was dispossessed twice... So my question is, if a site like Whoscored can lie so boldly about stats, can we really trust them at all?
